  - items[4]{impact,mitigation,severity,text}:
    Users with visual impairments cannot use the app comfortably,Run automated contrast checks and adjust tokens before merging,high,Dark mode color contrast may not meet WCAG AA standards
    Janky scrolling and reduced frame rate on older devices,Add a @supports check and fallback solid background,medium,Backdrop-filter performance on low-end hardware
    Users with motion sensitivity experience discomfort,Wrap animations in prefers-reduced-motion media query,medium,CSS animation conflicts with browser preference for reduced motion
    Single module type fails to render,All component templates are tested individually,low,Template variable name mismatch in one component
    heading: Risks & Mitigations
    type: risks
  - items[4]{text}:
    All users run modern browsers that support CSS custom properties
    The Go html/template rendering layer does not require JS for layout
    Plans will never exceed 50 modules per plan document
    Dark mode preference is detected via system-level media query only
